esqlQuery.esql:
// Alert when Kubernetes volume filesystem usage exceeds 80%.
//
// What triggers this alert:
// Volume used percentage above 0.8 (80%) — approaching capacity.
//
// What it means:
// Volume nearing capacity may cause write failures, pod evictions, or outages.
//
// Action needed:
// Expand volume, clean up data, or migrate workloads.
//
// Adjust threshold as needed (e.g., 0.9 for 90%).
TS metrics-kubernetes.volume-*
| WHERE `kubernetes.volume.fs.used.pct` > 0.8
| STATS doc_count = COUNT(*)
  BY `orchestrator.cluster.name`, `kubernetes.volume.name`, `kubernetes.namespace`
| WHERE doc_count > 0
